column1: #Text=Pride organisers apologise after protestors interrupt parade
#Text=Sunday , Pride in London organisers issued a public apology via their website condemning an unregistered lesbian protest group as " transphobic , hateful protestors who blocked the Pride " .

column1: #Text=The annual lesbian , gay , transgender and bisexual ( LGBT ) Pride in the English capital ended with roughly 30 thousand people participating in this year 's parade , organisers said .
#Text=A group of lesbians called " Get the L Out " protested in the parade with signs reading " Transactivism erases lesbians " , " Lesbian Not Queer " and " Lesbian = Female homosexual " .

#Text=The organisers called the  Get the L Out " group " transphobic " .

column1: #Text=The group was not expelled from the pride as they did not commit a criminal offence , organisers said .
#Text=By later report , Metropolitan Police allegedly refused to remove the " Get the L Out " group .
#Text=On Twitter , to counter the group , the hashtag of " #LwiththeT " surfaced .
#Text=Board member of TransPALS Patricia Curtis condemned the " hijack " of the Pride parade .

#Text=Condemning the incident , President of European Pride Organisers Association Kristine Garina said , " The Pride movement was begun by trans people and trans people must always be welcome at Pride " .
#Text=Garina continued , " Hate has no place at Pride , and we stand with the organisers who have promised to review what happened to try and ensure it cannot happen again .
#Text=Saturday 's parade started at Portland Place at noon and ended at Whitehall , the BBC reported , with 30 thousand people participating in the march from 472 organisations .
#Text=London mayor Sadiq Khan also participated in the pride parade .
#Text=" In London , you 're free to be who you are and you 're free to love who you want to love , and it 's really important we 're never complacent " , Khan said .
